A 47-year-old man was arrested for possession of dagga at Mnyameni Loc Ngqeleni near Mthatha in Eastern Cape on Wednesday afternoon.The police confirmed that the man was found with dagga weighing 91kg with an estimated street value of R91,000. They also confiscated more than 600 dagga plants in a joint operation.The alleged drug lord was arrested after the Provincial Operational Response Service, Border Police, SANDF, SA Navy and the Department of Agriculture and Forest conducted a search. He will appear in Mnyameni Magistrate Court tomorrow because he will be charged formally today(Thursday). The search continues and we are still going to arrest more, Eastern Cape police spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Mzukisi Fatyela told The New Age.-Hitekani Maimela